Scheme scripts go to <gimp-custom>/scripts
while python scripts go to <gimp-custom>/plug-ins,
where <gimp-custom> is <home>/.gimp-2.x for installation
or <gimp-portable-dir>/portable for Parhta's portable version.

Scripts placed in Python-Fu (Using the <code>menu</code> parameter of register(),
not the <code>label</code> argument! Specifying menu path in <code>label</code>
does imitate menu placement, but only in the GUI.) should not have the two implicit
arguments (image, drawable) declared in register(). Scripts placed elsewhere should,
though.